President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Cynthia L. Quarterman as the Administrator of the Pipeline and Hazardous Materials Safety Administration at the Department of Transportation. He also announced that Mary Lucille Jordan will be designated as the Chair of the Federal Mine Safety and Health Review Commission. President Obama expressed his gratitude to these individuals for choosing to serve in his administration and stated that he looks forward to working with them to strengthen safety and preparedness. Cynthia L. Quarterman is a partner at the law firm Steptoe & Johnson LLP in Washington, DC, with expertise in transportation and natural resources. Mary Lucille Jordan has previously served as Chair and Commissioner of the Federal Mine Safety and Health Review Commission and has a background in mine safety and health law.